// `lines` framing must also work when the downstream is an external command (a
// byte consumer), not just a typed stage like `parseInt`. The boundary is a
// byte pipe there, so `lines` writes each line back as `line\n` (rather than
// enqueuing typed values) — otherwise the executable reads an empty stdin and
// silently produces nothing. Here `lines | cat` round-trips the three lines.
{ echo "alpha"; echo "beta"; echo "gamma" } | lines | cat
